article.headline: Tigers poised to finish season winless
article.linkText: Losing cause: Savannah State drops to 0-27
article.story:
DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Antonio Webb scored 24 points to help Bethune-Cookman defeat Savannah State 78-69 on Friday night, bringing the Tigers within one loss of becoming the second winless Division I team in the last 50 years. Savannah State (0-27), a Division I independent, plays its season finale at home against Florida A&M on Monday. The Tigers lost 92-68 to Florida A&M on Feb. 2. The last winless Division I men's team was Prairie View A&M, which went 0-28 in 1991-92. Friday's loss matched Savannah State's second-closest final margin this season. Jacksonville beat the Tigers 73-67 on Nov. 27; Bethune-Cookman beat the Tigers 73-64 on Jan. 3.
All-time Division I Winless Teams
Season Team Record
1991-92 Prairie View 0-28
1917-18 Dartmouth 0-26
1936-37 William & Mary 0-18
Nicholas Berry added 16 for Bethune-Cookman (10-12), which has won four of its last six games and never trailed against the hapless Tigers. Mike Bennett led Savannah State with 20 points, with Donald Carson scoring 19 and Brandon Emerson adding 14. The Tigers, who held a 51-41 rebounding margin, got a game-high 15 rebounds from Sherard Reddick and 10 more from Emerson. Savannah State, with only eight scholarship players on its roster, ranks last out of 326 Division I men's teams in scoring defense, scoring margin, assists per game, and free throw percentage, and next-to-last in field-goal percentage. Webb scored 14 points in the first half, helping the Wildcats take a 17-point lead at the break. The lead stretched to 20 with 12:56 remaining, before Savannah State rallied and got within 70-62 with 2:33 left. Webb then scored six points in the last 1:27 to seal the win.
